The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring January 16, 2012, as Religious Freedom Day in the United States. It highlights the historical significance of religious freedom in America, referencing the Virginia Statute for Religious Freedom drafted by Thomas Jefferson in 1786. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of religious tolerance and pluralism in American society and reaffirms the commitment to protecting religious liberty both domestically and internationally. It calls on all Americans to commemorate the day with events and activities that promote understanding and protection of religious freedom.